<subSubSection id="C34AA9862179FF8A65DFE3C90410807D" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEFFA0D2179FF8A65DFE3C90410807D" blockId="1.[151,760,733,884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">
The genus comprises 275 species distributed all over the world. Many are common in the forest floor litter, mainly in the subtropics and tropics. Only one species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C50818E2179FF8A65FDE22B05A6805F" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1845" box="[151,253,831,854]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B924261F2179FF8A65FDE22B05A6805F" box="[151,253,831,854]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Baeocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known from 
<collectingRegion id="499434EF2179FF8A64AAE2290778805D" box="[448,547,829,852]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="1" pageNumber="152">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
, a second species is described below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34AA9862179FF8A66CBE7E7006C8402" box="[929,1335,1779,1803]" pageId="1" pageNumber="152" type="description">
